Because I think although people
know Make-A-Wish, they don't.

00:32:19.746 --> 00:32:22.000
I don't think they realize
how much we're just

00:32:22.000 --> 00:32:23.700
in your community
from day to day.

00:32:23.700 --> 00:32:27.824
So our summer campaign is
really off of the gala.

00:32:27.824 --> 00:32:29.740
One of the things we did
in the gala is really

00:32:29.740 --> 00:32:31.540
want to make sure that
everybody understood

00:32:31.540 --> 00:32:34.310
that what we're doing,
not just in New York

00:32:34.310 --> 00:32:37.050
or Make-A-Wish nationwide, but
really understand that we're

00:32:37.050 --> 00:32:39.280
in your community,
that these kids,

00:32:39.280 --> 00:32:40.850
they might be your
neighbors, or they

00:32:40.850 --> 00:32:44.100
might be somebody who your
children go to school with.

00:32:44.100 --> 00:32:46.690
And that it's really important
that everyone knows that they

00:32:46.690 --> 00:32:47.780
can play a part in it.

00:32:47.780 --> 00:32:50.420
We've done a lot of work to
try to get people to understand

00:32:50.420 --> 00:32:53.140
the impact and how that
goes through a community

00:32:53.140 --> 00:32:54.660
and how everyone's impacted.

00:32:54.660 --> 00:32:56.395
So what we did in
the gala is really

00:32:56.395 --> 00:32:58.270
start talking about the
boroughs and the work

00:32:58.270 --> 00:33:00.426
that we do in each
of the boroughs.

00:33:00.426 --> 00:33:02.050
In New York City we
have five boroughs.

00:33:02.050 --> 00:33:04.450
We also work in Nassau County,
and each of those Boroughs

00:33:04.450 --> 00:33:06.260
has a tremendous
group of hospitals,

00:33:06.260 --> 00:33:09.160
a tremendous amount of health
care workers who help us,

00:33:09.160 --> 00:33:10.950
volunteers who help us.

00:33:10.950 --> 00:33:12.710
The community that
usually, when they

00:33:12.710 --> 00:33:15.850
know a kid is sick in their
community, they rally around

00:33:15.850 --> 00:33:17.120
and help out.

00:33:17.120 --> 00:33:19.710
So we wanted to start really
going deeper into what

00:33:19.710 --> 00:33:20.850
that impact looks like.

00:33:20.850 --> 00:33:22.970
And so we talked about
the boroughs at our gala,

00:33:22.970 --> 00:33:25.450
and we brought that through
in a boroughs campaign.

00:33:25.450 --> 00:33:27.730
But it was really being
able to really look

00:33:27.730 --> 00:33:29.640
at summer is our busiest time.

00:33:29.640 --> 00:33:33.610
We have over 200 wishes to
grant this summer, which

00:33:33.610 --> 00:33:35.060
makes us internally very busy.

00:33:35.060 --> 00:33:37.080
But that means our
volunteers and our outreach,

00:33:37.080 --> 00:33:38.480
everything has to ramp up.

00:33:38.480 --> 00:33:40.430
Our fundraising has to ramp up.

00:33:40.430 --> 00:33:42.140
And we wanted
people to understand

00:33:42.140 --> 00:33:45.550
that it's really urgent.

00:33:45.550 --> 00:33:48.200
We say wishes can't wait because
these kids have gone through--

00:33:48.200 --> 00:33:50.722
quite often they've gone through
some tremendous treatment.

00:33:50.722 --> 00:33:52.180
They've gone through
months, if not

00:33:52.180 --> 00:33:55.720
years, of trying to get better
or deal with an illness.

00:33:55.720 --> 00:33:57.142
They've waited they.

00:33:57.142 --> 00:33:59.100
And they've been able to
get this wish granted.

00:33:59.100 --> 00:34:03.920
Sometimes it is that
case where they're

00:34:03.920 --> 00:34:06.270
looking at this wish all
along, and it helps them heal.

00:34:06.270 --> 00:34:07.590
It helps them with hope.

00:34:07.590 --> 00:34:09.491
It helps bring their
family back together

00:34:09.491 --> 00:34:11.449
when they're going through
a tremendous crisis.

00:34:11.449 --> 00:34:14.570
And quite often a wish
is that crowning piece

00:34:14.570 --> 00:34:16.860
that they get to go do
something with their family.

00:34:16.860 --> 00:34:20.131
And that happens a lot in the
summer because they can travel.

00:34:20.131 --> 00:34:21.880
So they can't wait
because these kids have

00:34:21.880 --> 00:34:24.000
gone through-- they've
gone through so much

00:34:24.000 --> 00:34:24.920
to get where they are.

00:34:24.920 --> 00:34:29.750
And we can't let them wait
another season to do that.

00:34:29.750 --> 00:34:34.940
But we also in our Wishes
Can't Wait campaign, each week,

00:34:34.940 --> 00:34:38.199
we take a story of
a child and tell you

00:34:38.199 --> 00:34:40.730
what they've gone through and
why their wish can't wait.

00:34:40.730 --> 00:34:44.120
And we tell it where the
borough that they're from

00:34:44.120 --> 00:34:45.848
and what the
hospitals are there,

00:34:45.848 --> 00:34:47.639
how they help us so
much with outreach, how

00:34:47.639 --> 00:34:51.510
those medical professionals
help us reach those kids

00:34:51.510 --> 00:34:54.060
and teach those kids
about what a wish can do,

00:34:54.060 --> 00:34:56.429
and about the volunteers
that are in the community.

00:34:56.429 --> 00:34:58.550
So we really try to tell a
little bit about each community

00:34:58.550 --> 00:34:59.050
as well.

00:34:59.050 --> 00:35:02.330
Again, really showing
everybody that it takes

00:35:02.330 --> 00:35:03.650
a lot of different people.

00:35:03.650 --> 00:35:08.119
And you can probably, in the
stories, find yourself in it.

00:35:08.119 --> 00:35:09.160
MATT TARGETT: Absolutely.

